SSJ.js - Make your text go super saiyin!!

Just what you were looking for - a jQuery plugin to add a super saiyin effect to your text. 

Some people might ask why... to them I say why not?!

DEFAULT OPTIONS:

	$.fn.ssj.defaults = {
        animateGlowTimeout: 180,  	//milliseconds between each glow animation
        powerLevelStyleRanges: [
        	//powering up...
        	{
        		maxClicks: 5,		//max clicks before moving to next style range
        		blurRadiusMax: 16,
        		blurRadiusMin: 12,
        		blurColor: '#3D85C6', //blueish color
        		incrementSize: 6
        	},
        	//SSJ!!
        	{				
	    		incrementSize: 20,
	    		blurRadiusMin: 18,
	    		blurRadiusMax: 27,
	    		blurColor: 'yellow',
	    		color: 'orange'
	    	}
        ]
	};


EXAMPLE:

	<body>
		<h1>SSJ.js</h1>
		<h2>Try clicking the robots</h2>
		<div class="robot hands-down">j</div>
		<div class="robot hands-up">i</div>
	</body>
	<script>
	//assuming you already have jQuery loaded here...
	//use default options
	$('.robot.hands-down').ssj();

	//a little more variation
	$('.robot.hands-up').ssj({
		powerLevelStyleRanges: [
	    	{
	    		maxClicks: 5,
	    		blurRadiusMax: 12,
	    		blurRadiusMin: 15,
	    		blurColor: 'red',
	    		incrementSize: 7
	    	},
	    	{
	    		maxClicks: 15,
	    		blurRadiusMin: 21,
	    		blurRadiusMax: 26,
	    		incrementSize: 10
	    	},
	    	{
	    		maxClicks: 20,
	    		incrementSize: 15
	    	},
	    	{
	    		incrementSize: 30,
	    		blurRadiusMin: 33,
	    		blurRadiusMax: 40,
	    		blurColor: 'yellow',
	    		color: 'orange'
	    	}
	    ]
	});

</script>